## General Business

Middle East Area of Operations Day

The annual commemoration will be held on 11 July.

- Planned as an evening event commencing approximately 5:00 pm.
- Similar format to last year’s event, including finger food and refreshments.

### Funeral Notifications

Members discussed the importance of notifying members when a member passes away and providing funeral details.

The Chair acknowledged improvements were needed and committed to ensuring members are advised of future funerals.

It was noted that Paradise FM also broadcasts funeral notices each morning.

### Veterans and Families Wellbeing Day

The Chair outlined an early proposal to hold a regional Veterans and Families Day in early 2027.

Concept includes:

- Family-friendly community event.
- Information stalls.
- Veteran advocates.
- DVA support services.
- Open Arms.
- My Aged Care representatives.
- Children’s activities.
- Food vendors.

Further planning and costings will be presented to members before any formal approval.

### Defence Property Sales

A member expressed concern regarding the Federal Government’s proposed disposal of Defence properties, particularly:

- Point Cook
- HMAS Penguin
- Victoria Barracks
  
Members were encouraged to raise concerns with local Members of Parliament where appropriate.

### DVA Clinical Care Funding

Members were advised of concerns regarding proposed limits on DVA clinical care funding, particularly the introduction of a reported $5,000 cap on certain clinical care arrangements.


Members were encouraged to remain informed of future developments.

